{
  "stem": "20021.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 391.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "For a young boy, say 16 or 17, who didn't speak Polish, who was very much German and wanted to be very much German, as many of the German Jews-- unlike the Polish Jews who-- who were proud of their Jewish identity, the German Jews were different.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were not-- they were trying to assimilate very strongly.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Right the next generation, the parents would come from Poland but the next generation really wanted to be German very much so.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And suddenly, their Jewish reality was forced upon them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so first, they had to cope with that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "For many of them, it was very difficult to accept.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Second, they found themselves in Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they kind of looked down on Poland, considered this an inferior country, including the Jews of Poland, who considered them inferior to themselves.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And yet here they were, dependent on those people whom they considered inferior to help them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So it was a-- quite a tragedy, considering the individual German Jew who found himself in that situation.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Plus they were deprived of all their possessions.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Hitler didn't let them take anything with them, barely clothes, you know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So they had to face great economic difficulties.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So it was a great tragedy for them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And to some extent [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] there is such an expression in Yiddish called [YIDDISH].",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "That expression implies a person who lacks practicality, who is not adaptable, who is sort of inflexible.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So that-- the Polish Jews, let's put it this way, were different.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They were much more adaptable.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They would get along.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And in the face of great difficulties, they would make up for the difficulties with jokes.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The German Jews-- I'm generalizing, of course-- were more serious.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They took their faith, so, you know, they were heartbroken.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
